    body: "The Old Testament Ark of the Covenant was the gold-covered chest containing the tablets of the Law, Aaron's rod, and manna — overshadowed by God's presence (the Shekinah). Catholic theology sees Mary as the fulfillment of this type: she carried within her womb not stone tablets but the Word made flesh, not Aaron's rod but the eternal High Priest, not manna but the Living Bread from heaven. Luke's account of the Visitation deliberately echoes 2 Samuel 6, David's transfer of the Ark: Mary 'arose and went' to the hill country as the Ark traveled to the hills of Judah; Elizabeth 'cried out' as David 'leaped'; Mary stayed three months as the Ark stayed three months. These parallels are too precise to be accidental.",
